         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne Botanical Gardens ¶ 2nd June 1862 ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ In reply to your letter dated 31st May, I have the honor to inform you, that I shall be happy to supply to your noble Institution such Plants, a...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.06.02c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Samuel<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Simmonds</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Minute book, Trustees of the Brighton General Cemetery,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Melbourne,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 81.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; "/>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. MS is a version copied into the minutes; M's given name is transcribed incorrectly.</p>
               </note>Melbourne Botanical Gardens</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">2nd June 1862</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your letter dated 31st May, I have the honor to inform you, that I shall be happy to supply to your noble Institution such Plants, as after the extensive distribution during the past month remain available. I can supply amongst other Plants Cypresses largely.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Will you be so good to send for whatever you require any morning at 9 and if possible within the next days.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>At the meeting of Trustees held 1 August 1862, Simmonds 'reported that Dr Mueller had kindly presented 500 Plants of various kinds, also a large packet of Seeds. also that Messrs Smith &amp; Adamson of Melbourne had presented Plants'. The Trustees resolved to thank M<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and Smith &amp; Adamson<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>their<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'liberality' (p. 81a).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>There is a copy of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>letter Simmonds sent to Smith &amp; Adamson on 12 August annotated: 'a similar letter to the above was also written to Dr Mueller'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>For M's reply, see M to S. Simmonds, 16 August 1862 (in this edition as 62-08-16c).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Fred. Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">S P Simmonds</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Secretary to the Cemetery of Brighton</p>
         </div>
